mscTraceRcvrX25RowStatusTable.description: This entry controls the addition and deletion of mscTraceRcvrX25 components.

mscTraceRcvrX25RowStatusEntry.description: A single entry in the table represents a single mscTraceRcvrX25 component.

mscTraceRcvrX25RowStatus.description: This variable is used as the basis for SNMP naming of mscTraceRcvrX25 components. These components can be added and deleted.

mscTraceRcvrX25ComponentName.description: This variable provides the component's string name for use with the ASCII Console Interface

mscTraceRcvrX25StorageType.description: This variable represents the storage type value for the mscTraceRcvrX25 tables.

mscTraceRcvrX25Index.name: mscTraceRcvrX25Index
mscTraceRcvrX25Index.description: This variable represents the index for the mscTraceRcvrX25 tables.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaRowStatusTable.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaRowStatusTable
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaRowStatusTable.description: This entry controls the addition and deletion of mscTraceRcvrX25Dna components.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaRowStatusEntry.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaRowStatusEntry
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaRowStatusEntry.description: A single entry in the table represents a single mscTraceRcvrX25Dna component.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaRowStatus.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaRowStatus
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaRowStatus.description: This variable is used as the basis for SNMP naming of mscTraceRcvrX25Dna components. These components cannot be added nor deleted.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaComponentName.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaComponentName
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaComponentName.description: This variable provides the component's string name for use with the ASCII Console Interface

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaStorageType.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaStorageType
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaStorageType.description: This variable represents the storage type value for the mscTraceRcvrX25Dna tables.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaIndex.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaIndex
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaIndex.description: This variable represents the index for the mscTraceRcvrX25Dna tables.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaAddressTable.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaAddressTable
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaAddressTable.description: This group contains attributes common to all Dnas. This group is composed of two attributes which define a Dna. These attributes are used to interpret the format of the address digits.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaNumberingPlanIndicator.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaNumberingPlanIndicator
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaNumberingPlanIndicator.description: This attribute indicates the Numbering Plan Indicator (NPI) of the Dna that is entered. The address may belong to an E.164 or X.121 plan.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaDataNetworkAddress.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaDataNetworkAddress
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaDataNetworkAddress.description: The Dna attribute contains digits which form a unique identifier for the calling end of the trace connection. Dna digits are selected and assigned by network operators. The maximum Dna length is 15 digits.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaOutgoingOptionsTable.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaOutgoingOptionsTable
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaOutgoingOptionsTable.description: This group defines call options for outgoing calls.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaOutCalls.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaOutCalls
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaOutCalls.description: This attribute specifies that outgoing calls (from the DTE to the network) can be made using this particular Dna component.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaOutDefaultPriority.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaOutDefaultPriority
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaOutDefaultPriority.description: If this attribute is set to normal, then the default priority for outgoing calls (from the DTE to the network) using this particular Dna is normal priority when the priority is not specified in the call. If this attribute is set to high then the default priority for outgoing calls using this particular Dna is high priority.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaOutIntl.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaOutIntl
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaOutIntl.description: This attribute specifies that outgoing international calls (from the DTE to the network) can be made using this particular Dna. This attribute also controls access to another numbering plan, and specifies that cross-numbering plan calls are allowed.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaOutDefaultPathSensitiv.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaOutDefaultPathSensitivity
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaOutDefaultPathSensitiv.description: This attribute specifies the default class of routing (delay/ throughput) for all outgoing calls (from the DTE to the network) using this particular Dna. The chosen default class of routing applies to all outgoing calls established using this Dna, and applies to the packets travelling in both directions on all outgoing calls (local to remote, and remote to local). This attribute, if set to a value of throughput, specifies that the default class of routing is throughput sensitive. If set to a value of delay, then the default class of routing is delay sensitive. This attribute is obsoleted. Please refer to defaultTransferPriority for the corresponding new attribute.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaOutDefaultPathReliabil.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaOutDefaultPathReliability
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaOutDefaultPathReliabil.description: This attribute specifies the default reliability class of routing for all calls (from the DTE to the network) using this particular Dna. The chosen default reliability class of routing normally applies to all packets (including the call packets) travelling into the network. A value of high specifies that packets are to be overflowed or retransmitted at various routing levels. Typically high reliability results in duplication and disordering of packets in the network, when errors are detected or during link congestion. The VC handles the duplication and disordering to ensure that packets are delivered to the interface in the proper sequence and without duplication.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaOutPathReliabilityOver.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaOutPathReliabilityOverRide
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaOutPathReliabilityOver.description: This attribute specifies that the called end of the connection will not use the calling end provisioning data for reliability class of routing to override the provisioning data at the called end.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaOutPathReliabilitySign.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaOutPathReliabilitySignal
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaOutPathReliabilitySign.description: This attribute specifies that reliability routing signaling is not used.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaOutAccess.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaOutAccess
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaOutAccess.description: This attribute is an extension of the Closed User Group (CUG) facility. If this attribute is set to a value of allowed, it specifies that outgoing calls (from the DTE to the network) to the open (non- CUG) part of the network are permitted. It also permits outgoing calls to interfaces that have Incoming Access capabilities. If set to a value of disallowed, then such calls cannot be made using this Dna (the calls will be cleared by the local DCE). This attribute corresponds to the ITU-T 'Closed User Group with Outgoing Access' feature.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaIncomingOptionsTable.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaIncomingOptionsTable
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaIncomingOptionsTable.description: This group defines the call options for incoming calls.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaIncCalls.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaIncCalls
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaIncCalls.description: This attribute specifies that incoming calls (from the network to the DTE) cannot be made to this Dna.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCallOptionsTable.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCallOptionsTable
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCallOptionsTable.description: The CallOptions group defines additional options for calls which are not specific to the direction of the call.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaPacketSizes.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaPacketSizes
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaPacketSizes.description: This attribute specifies the allowable packet sizes supported for calls using this Dna. Description of bits: n16(0) n32(1) n64(2) n128(3) n256(4) n512(5) n1024(6) n2048(7) n4096(8)

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaDefaultRecvFrmNetworkP.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaDefaultRecvFrmNetworkPacketSize
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaDefaultRecvFrmNetworkP.description: This attribute specifies the default local receive packet size from network to DTE for calls using this particular Dna.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaDefaultSendToNetworkPa.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaDefaultSendToNetworkPacketSize
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaDefaultSendToNetworkPa.description: This attribute specifies the default local send packet size from DTE to network for all calls using this particular Dna.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaDefaultRecvFrmNetworkT.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaDefaultRecvFrmNetworkThruputClass
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaDefaultRecvFrmNetworkT.description: This attribute specifies the default receive throughput class, (towards the interface) for all calls using this particular Dna.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaDefaultSendToNetworkTh.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaDefaultSendToNetworkThruputClass
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaDefaultSendToNetworkTh.description: This attribute specifies the default send throughput class (towards the network) for all calls using this particular Dna.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaDefaultRecvFrmNetworkW.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaDefaultRecvFrmNetworkWindowSize
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaDefaultRecvFrmNetworkW.description: This attribute specifies the default value for the number of data packets that can be send to the interface before any acknowledgment.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaDefaultSendToNetworkWi.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaDefaultSendToNetworkWindowSize
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaDefaultSendToNetworkWi.description: This attribute specifies the default value for the number of data packets that can be received from the interface before any acknowledgment.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaPacketSizeNegotiation.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaPacketSizeNegotiation
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaPacketSizeNegotiation.description: This attribute, if set to local specifies that packet sizes can be negotiated locally at the interface irrespective of the setting at the remote interface. If set to endtoEnd, then the packet size negotiation is between the local and remote interface (i.e. packet sizes are the same on both interfaces).

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugFormat.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugFormat
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugFormat.description: This attribute specifies the format to signal CUG indices as basic or extended. A basic CUG index format is two digits long. An extended CUG index format is four digits long.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugRowStatusTable.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugRowStatusTable
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugRowStatusTable.description: This entry controls the addition and deletion of mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCug components.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugRowStatusEntry.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugRowStatusEntry
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugRowStatusEntry.description: A single entry in the table represents a single mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCug component.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugRowStatus.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugRowStatus
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugRowStatus.description: This variable is used as the basis for SNMP naming of mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCug components. These components can be added and deleted.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugComponentName.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugComponentName
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugComponentName.description: This variable provides the component's string name for use with the ASCII Console Interface

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugStorageType.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugStorageType
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugStorageType.description: This variable represents the storage type value for the mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCug tables.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugIndex.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugIndex
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugIndex.description: This variable represents the index for the mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCug tables.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugCugOptionsTable.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugCugOptionsTable
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugCugOptionsTable.description: Attributes in this group define ClosedUserGroup options associated with interlockCode. Dnas with the same CUG (interlockCode) can make calls within this group. Various combinations of attributes are defined under this option which permit or prevent calls in the same CUG group.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugType.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugType
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugType.description: This attribute specifies the CUG type as either national or international. A national CUG has significance within the local network only. An international CUG has significance across network boundaries.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugDnic.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugDnic
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugDnic.description: This attribute specifies the Data Network ID Code of the network that is administering the international CUG. This attribute is not used for a national CUG and should be left at its default value. The dnic value is not an arbitrary number. It is assigned by international agreement and controlled by ITU-T.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugInterlockCode.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugInterlockCode
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugInterlockCode.description: This attribute specifies a numeric identifier of a national or international closed user group. It is an arbitrary number. This attribute may also be called CUG in some descriptions. Dnas defined with this number can only make calls to Dnas defined with the same interlockCode.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugPreferential.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugPreferential
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugPreferential.description: This attribute specifies that this Cug is to be used on all outgoing calls to the X.25 trace receiver.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugOutCalls.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugOutCalls
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugOutCalls.description: This attribute specifies that outgoing calls (from the DTE into the network) can be made using this particular Cug.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugIncCalls.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugIncCalls
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugIncCalls.description: This attribute specifies that incoming calls (from the network to the DTE) cannot be accepted using this Cug.

mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugPrivileged.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugPrivileged
mscTraceRcvrX25DnaCugPrivileged.description: This attribute specifies that this Cug is privileged. For a call between two closed user group Dnas to connect, at least one Dna must have a privileged Cug.

mscTraceRcvrX25DcRowStatusTable.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DcRowStatusTable
mscTraceRcvrX25DcRowStatusTable.description: This entry controls the addition and deletion of mscTraceRcvrX25Dc components.

mscTraceRcvrX25DcRowStatusEntry.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DcRowStatusEntry
mscTraceRcvrX25DcRowStatusEntry.description: A single entry in the table represents a single mscTraceRcvrX25Dc component.

mscTraceRcvrX25DcRowStatus.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DcRowStatus
mscTraceRcvrX25DcRowStatus.description: This variable is used as the basis for SNMP naming of mscTraceRcvrX25Dc components. These components cannot be added nor deleted.

mscTraceRcvrX25DcComponentName.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DcComponentName
mscTraceRcvrX25DcComponentName.description: This variable provides the component's string name for use with the ASCII Console Interface

mscTraceRcvrX25DcStorageType.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DcStorageType
mscTraceRcvrX25DcStorageType.description: This variable represents the storage type value for the mscTraceRcvrX25Dc tables.

mscTraceRcvrX25DcIndex.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DcIndex
mscTraceRcvrX25DcIndex.description: This variable represents the index for the mscTraceRcvrX25Dc tables.

mscTraceRcvrX25DcOptionsTable.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DcOptionsTable
mscTraceRcvrX25DcOptionsTable.description: The Options group defines attributes associated with the SVC direct call.

mscTraceRcvrX25DcRemoteNpi.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DcRemoteNpi
mscTraceRcvrX25DcRemoteNpi.description: This attribute indicates the numbering plan used for the remoteDna.

mscTraceRcvrX25DcRemoteDna.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DcRemoteDna
mscTraceRcvrX25DcRemoteDna.description: This attribute specifies the Data Network Address of the remote end of the connection. This is the DNA of the X.25 trace receiver which will receive the trace data.

mscTraceRcvrX25DcType.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DcType
mscTraceRcvrX25DcType.description: This attribute specifies the type of call as switched. For a switched call, no information is defined at the remote end about the local end of the connection.

mscTraceRcvrX25DcUserData.name: mscTraceRcvrX25DcUserData
mscTraceRcvrX25DcUserData.description: This attribute contains the user data. It is a 0 to 16 byte length string which is appended to the call request packet that is presented to the called (destination) DTE.

mscTraceSessionX25RowStatusTable.name: mscTraceSessionX25RowStatusTable
mscTraceSessionX25RowStatusTable.description: *** THIS TABLE CURRENTLY NOT IMPLEMENTED *** This entry controls the addition and deletion of mscTraceSessionX25 components.

mscTraceSessionX25RowStatusEntry.name: mscTraceSessionX25RowStatusEntry
mscTraceSessionX25RowStatusEntry.description: A single entry in the table represents a single mscTraceSessionX25 component.

mscTraceSessionX25RowStatus.name: mscTraceSessionX25RowStatus
mscTraceSessionX25RowStatus.description: This variable is used as the basis for SNMP naming of mscTraceSessionX25 components. These components cannot be added nor deleted.

mscTraceSessionX25ComponentName.name: mscTraceSessionX25ComponentName
mscTraceSessionX25ComponentName.description: This variable provides the component's string name for use with the ASCII Console Interface

mscTraceSessionX25StorageType.name: mscTraceSessionX25StorageType
mscTraceSessionX25StorageType.description: This variable represents the storage type value for the mscTraceSessionX25 tables.

mscTraceSessionX25Index.name: mscTraceSessionX25Index
mscTraceSessionX25Index.description: This variable represents the index for the mscTraceSessionX25 tables.

mscTraceSessionX25VcRowStatusTable.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcRowStatusTable
mscTraceSessionX25VcRowStatusTable.description: *** THIS TABLE CURRENTLY NOT IMPLEMENTED *** This entry controls the addition and deletion of mscTraceSessionX25Vc components.

mscTraceSessionX25VcRowStatusEntry.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcRowStatusEntry
mscTraceSessionX25VcRowStatusEntry.description: A single entry in the table represents a single mscTraceSessionX25Vc component.

mscTraceSessionX25VcRowStatus.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcRowStatus
mscTraceSessionX25VcRowStatus.description: This variable is used as the basis for SNMP naming of mscTraceSessionX25Vc components. These components cannot be added nor deleted.

mscTraceSessionX25VcComponentName.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcComponentName
mscTraceSessionX25VcComponentName.description: This variable provides the component's string name for use with the ASCII Console Interface

mscTraceSessionX25VcStorageType.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcStorageType
mscTraceSessionX25VcStorageType.description: This variable represents the storage type value for the mscTraceSessionX25Vc tables.

mscTraceSessionX25VcIndex.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcIndex
mscTraceSessionX25VcIndex.description: This variable represents the index for the mscTraceSessionX25Vc tables.

mscTraceSessionX25VcCadTable.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcCadTable
mscTraceSessionX25VcCadTable.description: *** THIS TABLE CURRENTLY NOT IMPLEMENTED *** This group represents operational call data related to General Vc. It can be displayed only for General Vc which is created by application.

mscTraceSessionX25VcType.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcType
mscTraceSessionX25VcType.description: This attribute displays the type of call, pvc or svc. type is provided at provisioning time.

mscTraceSessionX25VcState.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcState
mscTraceSessionX25VcState.description: This attribute displays the state of call control. P5 state is not supported but is listed for completness. Transitions from one state to another take very short time. state most often displayed is dataTransferP4.

mscTraceSessionX25VcPreviousState.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcPreviousState
mscTraceSessionX25VcPreviousState.description: This attribute displays the previous state of call control. This is a valuable field to determine how the processing is progressing.

mscTraceSessionX25VcDiagnosticCode.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcDiagnosticCode
mscTraceSessionX25VcDiagnosticCode.description: This attribute displays the internal substate of call control. It is used to further refine state of call processing.

mscTraceSessionX25VcPreviousDiagnosticCo.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcPreviousDiagnosticCode
mscTraceSessionX25VcPreviousDiagnosticCo.description: This attribute displays the internal substate of call control. It is used to further refine state of call processing.

mscTraceSessionX25VcCalledNpi.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcCalledNpi
mscTraceSessionX25VcCalledNpi.description: This attribute displays the Numbering Plan Indicator (NPI) of the called end.

mscTraceSessionX25VcCalledDna.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcCalledDna
mscTraceSessionX25VcCalledDna.description: This attribute displays the Data Network Address (Dna) of the called (destination) DTE to which this call is sent. This address if defined at recieving end will complete Vc connection.

mscTraceSessionX25VcCalledLcn.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcCalledLcn
mscTraceSessionX25VcCalledLcn.description: This attribute displays the Logical Channel Number of the called end. It is valid only after both ends of Vc exchanged relevant information.

mscTraceSessionX25VcCallingNpi.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcCallingNpi
mscTraceSessionX25VcCallingNpi.description: This attribute displays the Numbering Plan Indicator (NPI) of the calling end.

mscTraceSessionX25VcCallingDna.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcCallingDna
mscTraceSessionX25VcCallingDna.description: This attribute displays the Data Network Address (Dna) of the calling end.

mscTraceSessionX25VcCallingLcn.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcCallingLcn
mscTraceSessionX25VcCallingLcn.description: This attribute displays the Logical Channel Number of the calling end.

mscTraceSessionX25VcAccountingEnabled.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcAccountingEnabled
mscTraceSessionX25VcAccountingEnabled.description: This attribute indicates that this optional section of accounting record is suppressed or permitted. If accountingEnabled is yes, conditions for generation of accounting record were met. These conditions include billing options, vc recovery conditions and Module wide accounting data options.

mscTraceSessionX25VcFastSelectCall.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcFastSelectCall
mscTraceSessionX25VcFastSelectCall.description: This attribute displays that this is a fast select call.

mscTraceSessionX25VcLocalRxPktSize.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcLocalRxPktSize
mscTraceSessionX25VcLocalRxPktSize.description: This attribute displays the locally negotiated size of send packets.

mscTraceSessionX25VcLocalTxPktSize.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcLocalTxPktSize
mscTraceSessionX25VcLocalTxPktSize.description: This attribute displays the locally negotiated size of send packets.

mscTraceSessionX25VcLocalTxWindowSize.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcLocalTxWindowSize
mscTraceSessionX25VcLocalTxWindowSize.description: This attribute displays the send window size provided on incoming call packets or the default when a call request packet does not explicitly provide the window size.

mscTraceSessionX25VcLocalRxWindowSize.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcLocalRxWindowSize
mscTraceSessionX25VcLocalRxWindowSize.description: This attribute displays the receive window size provided on incoming call packets or the default when a call request does not explicitly provide the window sizes.

mscTraceSessionX25VcPathReliability.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcPathReliability
mscTraceSessionX25VcPathReliability.description: This attribute displays the path reliability.

mscTraceSessionX25VcAccountingEnd.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcAccountingEnd
mscTraceSessionX25VcAccountingEnd.description: This attribute indicates if this end should generate an accounting record. Normally, callingEnd is the end to generate an accounting record.

mscTraceSessionX25VcPriority.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcPriority
mscTraceSessionX25VcPriority.description: This attribute displays whether the call is a normal or a high priority call.

mscTraceSessionX25VcSegmentSize.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcSegmentSize
mscTraceSessionX25VcSegmentSize.description: This attribute displays the segment size (in bytes) used on the call. It is used to calculate the number of segments transmitted and received.

mscTraceSessionX25VcSubnetTxPktSize.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcSubnetTxPktSize
mscTraceSessionX25VcSubnetTxPktSize.description: This attribute displays the locally negotiated size of the data packets on this Vc.

mscTraceSessionX25VcSubnetTxWindowSize.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcSubnetTxWindowSize
mscTraceSessionX25VcSubnetTxWindowSize.description: This attribute displays the current send window size of Vc.

mscTraceSessionX25VcSubnetRxPktSize.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcSubnetRxPktSize
mscTraceSessionX25VcSubnetRxPktSize.description: This attribute displays the locally negotiated size of receive packets.

mscTraceSessionX25VcSubnetRxWindowSize.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcSubnetRxWindowSize
mscTraceSessionX25VcSubnetRxWindowSize.description: This attribute displays the receive window size provided on incoming call packets and to the default when a call request does not explicitly provide the window sizes.

mscTraceSessionX25VcMaxSubnetPktSize.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcMaxSubnetPktSize
mscTraceSessionX25VcMaxSubnetPktSize.description: This attribute displays the maximum packet size allowed on Vc.

mscTraceSessionX25VcTransferPriorityToNe.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcTransferPriorityToNetwork
mscTraceSessionX25VcTransferPriorityToNe.description: This attribute displays the priority in which data is transferred to the network. The transfer priority is a preference specified by an application according to its delay-sensitivity requirement. Frames with high transfer priority are served by the network before the frames with normal priority. Each transfer priority contains a predetermined setting for trunk queue (interrupting, delay or throughput), and routing metric (delay or throughput). When the transfer priority is set at high, the trunk queue is set to high, the routing metric is set to delay. When the transfer priority is set at normal, the trunk queue is set to normal, the routing metric is set to throughput.

mscTraceSessionX25VcTransferPriorityFrom.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcTransferPriorityFromNetwork
mscTraceSessionX25VcTransferPriorityFrom.description: This attribute displays the priority in which data is transferred from the network. The transfer priority is a preference specified by an application according to its delay-sensitivity requirement. Frames with high transfer priority are served by the network before the frames with normal priority. Each transfer priority contains a predetermined setting for trunk queue (interrupting, delay or throughput), and routing metric (delay or throughput). When the transfer priority is set at high, and the trunk queue is set to high, the routing metric is set to delay. When the transfer priority is set at normal, the trunk queue is set to normal, and the routing metric is set to throughput.

mscTraceSessionX25VcIntdTable.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcIntdTable
mscTraceSessionX25VcIntdTable.description: *** THIS TABLE CURRENTLY NOT IMPLEMENTED *** This group defines display of interval data collected by Vc. Data in this group is variable and may depend on time when this display command is issued.

mscTraceSessionX25VcCallReferenceNumber.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcCallReferenceNumber
mscTraceSessionX25VcCallReferenceNumber.description: This attribute is obsolete. It is replaced by the callReferenceNumber attribute to display the call reference number in decimal. The SNMP reference for the callReferenceNumber attribute is callReferenceNumberDecimal.

mscTraceSessionX25VcElapsedTimeTillNow.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcElapsedTimeTillNow
mscTraceSessionX25VcElapsedTimeTillNow.description: This attribute displays the elapsed time representing the period of this interval data. It is elapsed time in 0.1 second increments since Vc started.

mscTraceSessionX25VcSegmentsRx.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcSegmentsRx
mscTraceSessionX25VcSegmentsRx.description: This attribute displays the number of segments received at the time command was issued. This is the segment received count maintained by accounting at each end of the Vc. This counter is updated only when the packet cannot be successfully delivered out of the sink Vc and to the sink AP Conditions in which packets may be discarded by the sink Vc include: missing packets due to subnet discards, segmentation protocol violations due to subnet discard, duplicated and out-of-ranged packets and packets that arrive while Vc is in path recovery state.

mscTraceSessionX25VcSegmentsSent.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcSegmentsSent
mscTraceSessionX25VcSegmentsSent.description: This attribute displays the number of segments sent at the time command was issued. This is the segment sent count maintained by accounting at the source Vc. Vc only counts packets that Vc thinks can be delivered successfully into the subnet. In reality, these packets may be dropped by trunking, for instance. This counter is not updated when splitting fails, when Vc is in a path recovery state, when packet forwarding fails to forward this packet and when subsequent packets have to be discarded as we want to minimize the chance of out-of-sequence and do not intentionally send out-of- sequenced packets into the subnet.

mscTraceSessionX25VcStartTime.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcStartTime
mscTraceSessionX25VcStartTime.description: This attribute displays the start time of this interval period. If Vc spans 12 hour time or time of day change startTime reflects new time as recorded at 12 hour periods or time of day changes.

mscTraceSessionX25VcCallReferenceNumberD.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcCallReferenceNumberDecimal
mscTraceSessionX25VcCallReferenceNumberD.description: This attribute displays the call reference number which is a unique number generated by the switch.The same Call Reference Number is stored in the interval data (accounting record) at both ends of the call. It can be used as one of the attributes in matching duplicate records generated at each end of the call.

mscTraceSessionX25VcStatsTable.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcStatsTable
mscTraceSessionX25VcStatsTable.description: *** THIS TABLE CURRENTLY NOT IMPLEMENTED *** ... Statistics(Stats) This group defines general attributes collected by general Vc. The purpose of Vc attributes is to aid end users and verification people to understand the Vc internal behavior. This is particularly useful when the network has experienced abnormality and we want to isolate problems and pinpoint trouble spots. Attributes are collected on a per Vc basis. Until a need is identified, statistics are not collected at a processor level. Each attribute is stored in a 32 bit field and is initialized to zero when a Vc enters into the data transfer state. When a PVC is disconnected and then connected again, the attributes will be reset. Attributes cannot be reset through other methods.

mscTraceSessionX25VcAckStackingTimeouts.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcAckStackingTimeouts
mscTraceSessionX25VcAckStackingTimeouts.description: This attribute counts the number of ack stacking timer expiries. It is used as an indicator of the acknowledgment behavior across the subnet when ack stacking is in effect. If it expires often, usually this means end users will experience longer delay. The ack stacking timer specifies how long the Vc will wait before finally sending the subnet acknowledgment. if this attribute is set to a value of 0, then the Vc will automatically return acknowledgment packets without delay. If this attribute is set to a value other than zero, then the Vc will wait for this amount of time in an attempt to piggyback the acknowledgment packet on another credit or data packet. If the Vc cannot piggyback the acknowledgment packet within this time, then the packet is returned without piggybacking.

mscTraceSessionX25VcOutOfRangeFrmFromSub.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcOutOfRangeFrmFromSubnet
mscTraceSessionX25VcOutOfRangeFrmFromSub.description: This attribute counts the number of subnet frames discarded due to the sequence number being out of range. Two Categories apply for the General Vc 1) lost Acks (previous Range) 2) unexpected Packets (next Range) Vc internally maintains its own sequence number of packet order and sequencing. Due to packet retransmission, Vc may receive duplicate packets that have the same Vc internal sequence number. Only 1 copy is accepted by the Vc and other copies of the same packets are detected through this count. This attribute can be used to record the frequency of packet retransmission due to Vc and other part of the subnet.

mscTraceSessionX25VcDuplicatesFromSubnet.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcDuplicatesFromSubnet
mscTraceSessionX25VcDuplicatesFromSubnet.description: This attribute counts the number of subnet packets discarded due to duplication. It is used to detect software error fault or duplication caused by retransmitting.

mscTraceSessionX25VcFrmRetryTimeouts.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcFrmRetryTimeouts
mscTraceSessionX25VcFrmRetryTimeouts.description: This attribute counts the number of frames which have retransmission time-out. If packets from Vc into the subnet are discarded by the subnet, the source Vc will not receive any acknowledgment. The retransmission timer then expires and packets will be retransmitted again. Note that the Vc idle probe may be retransmitted and is included in this count. This statistics does not show the distribution of how many times packets are retransmitted (e.g. first retransmission results in successful packet forwarding).

mscTraceSessionX25VcPeakRetryQueueSize.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcPeakRetryQueueSize
mscTraceSessionX25VcPeakRetryQueueSize.description: This attribute indicates the peak size of the retransmission queue. This attribute is used as an indicator of the acknowledgment behavior across the subnet. It records the largest body of unacknowledged packets.

mscTraceSessionX25VcPeakOoSeqQueueSize.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcPeakOoSeqQueueSize
mscTraceSessionX25VcPeakOoSeqQueueSize.description: This attribute indicates the peak size of the out of sequence queue. This attribute is used as an indicator of the sequencing behavior across the subnet. It records the largest body of out of sequence packets.

mscTraceSessionX25VcPeakOoSeqFrmForwarde.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcPeakOoSeqFrmForwarded
mscTraceSessionX25VcPeakOoSeqFrmForwarde.description: This attribute indicates the peak size of the sequence packet queue. This attribute is used as an indicator of the sequencing behavior across the subnet. It records the largest body of out of sequence packets, which by the receipt of an expected packet have been transformed to expected packets. The number of times this peak is reached is not recorded as it is traffic dependent.

mscTraceSessionX25VcPeakStackedAcksRx.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcPeakStackedAcksRx
mscTraceSessionX25VcPeakStackedAcksRx.description: This attribute indicates the peak size of wait acks. This attribute is used as an indicator of the acknowledgment behavior across the subnet. It records the largest collective acknowledgment.

mscTraceSessionX25VcSubnetRecoveries.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcSubnetRecoveries
mscTraceSessionX25VcSubnetRecoveries.description: This attribute counts the number of successful Vc recovery attempts. This attribute is used as an indicator of how many times the Vc path is broken but can be recovered. This attribute is useful to record the number of network path failures.

mscTraceSessionX25VcWindowClosuresToSubn.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcWindowClosuresToSubnet
mscTraceSessionX25VcWindowClosuresToSubn.description: This attribute counts the number of window closures to subnet. A packet may have been sent into the subnet but its acknowledgment from the remote Vc has not yet been received. This is a 8 bit sequence number.This number is useful in detecting whether the Vc is sending any packet into the subnet.

mscTraceSessionX25VcWindowClosuresFromSu.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcWindowClosuresFromSubnet
mscTraceSessionX25VcWindowClosuresFromSu.description: This attribute counts the number of window closures from subnet. This attribute is useful in detecting whether the Vc is receiving any packet from the subnet.

mscTraceSessionX25VcWrTriggers.name: mscTraceSessionX25VcWrTriggers
mscTraceSessionX25VcWrTriggers.description: This attribute displays the number of times the Vc stays within the W-R region. The W-R region is a value used to determined the timing of credit transmission. Should the current window size be beneath this value, the credits will be transmitted immediately. Otherwise, they will be transmitted later with actual data. The wrTriggers statistic is therefore used to analyze the flow control and credit mechanism.
